The paper discusses the application of convolutional neural networks (ConvNets) to predict compound activity from their Kekule structure representations. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) as ConvNets are a type of deep learning model commonly used in image analysis. The paper also involves the use of neural networks for prediction tasks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of different models and architectures, which falls under the category of computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of prediction errors, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
